apers (proposing new techniques):\n   вњ“ Implement baselines first (simpler methods, prior work)\n   вњ“ Implement proposed method\n   вњ“ Establish performance floor to validate evaluation pipeline\n\n   For BENCHMARK/EVALUATION papers (new datasets or metrics):\n   вњ“ Implement evaluation harness\n   вњ“ Test on existing models/methods\n   вњ“ Validate metric properties (reliability, discriminability)\n   вњ“ Compare to existing benchmarks if applicable\n\n   For ANALYSIS papers (understanding phenomena):\n   вњ“ Implement measurement/analysis tools\n   вњ“ Design controlled experiments or ablations\n   вњ“ Test hypotheses systematically\n\n   General best practices:\n   вњ“ Write modular, well-commented code\n   вњ“ Implement one component at a time\n   вњ“ Test each component independently\n   вњ“ Log intermediate results\n   вњ“ Save checkpoints frequently\n   вњ“ Use descriptive variable names\n   вњ“ Add assertions to validate assumptions\n\n5. Error Handling\n   вњ“ Use try-except blocks for robustness\n   вњ“ Log errors with full context\n   вњ“ Don&#39;t ignore warnings - investigate them\n   вњ“ Validate assumptions with assertions\n   вњ“ Handle edge cases gracefully\n\n6. Iterative Development\n   вњ“ Start small - validate on tiny dataset first\n   вњ“ Gradually scale up\n   вњ“ Monitor resource usage\n   вњ“ Checkpoint before long-running operations\n   вњ“ Document deviations from plan\n\nBEST PRACTICES:\n\nвњ“ DO: Start small and validate incrementally\nвњ“ DO: Print shapes and statistics frequently\nвњ“ DO: Visualize intermediate results\nвњ“ DO: Save outputs incrementally (don&#39;t wait until end)\nвњ“ DO: Make experiments reproducible (random seeds, versions)\nвњ“ DO: Comment complex logic immediately\nвњ“ DO: Separate data processing, modeling, and evaluation\n\nвњ— DON&#39;T: Hardcode paths or magic numbers\nвњ— DON&#39;T: Skip validation steps\nвњ— DON&#39;T: Ignore failed assertions or warnings\nвњ— DON&#39;T: Run long experiments without 